# Data model

## IDs

- `document`, `category`, `tag`: `uuid().primaryKey().defaultRandom()`
- `site_settings`: singleton row `id = 'default'`

## Tables

- `category` — name, sort order (managed in admin); public URLs use `id`
- `document` — title, content (markdown body or optional notes for media pages), `contentType` (`markdown` | `pdf` | `video` | `audio` | `image` | `office`, default `markdown`), `mediaUrl` (`http://` or `https://` URL when not markdown), excerpt, published, categoryId; public URLs use `id`
- `tag` + `document_tag` — many-to-many tags on documents (`document_tag` uses a UUID primary key with a unique pair index on document + tag); tags matched by unique `name`
- `site_settings` — site branding, landing hero, defaults

## Migrations

- Use `npm run db:generate` then `npm run db:push` for schema changes

## Routing IDs

- Public docs routes use UUID `id` path params (`/docs/[id]`, `/docs/category/[id]`)
- No DB `slug` columns on category, document, or tag; `slugify()` is only for markdown heading anchors
